  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.HU4lNUAme2XmxfAN]{Weapon Group: Small Arms, One-Handed}</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">This item employs a chemical irritant like capsaicin (common in some fruits, plants, and most chilies), also known as a lachrymatory agent. When a target is struck, a sticky, waxy, colorless and odorless liquid adheres to the skin. The spray contains almost pure capsaicin, with a Scoville rating of more than 10,000,000 â€“ double</span>&nbsp; <span class=\"fontstyle0\">the intensity of pepper spray. [Bear spray is 3,600,000 Scoville; pepper spray is 5,300,000&nbsp;</span>Scoville].</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If struck, the target must make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or be poisoned for 2d4 rounds. If you score a critical hit, the target fails this save. Larger creatures gain a bonus to the save as follows (+2 Large, +4 Huge; larger creatures are immune).</span></p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 64px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Capsicum spray </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 22px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">55 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 51px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Special </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 43px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">10/40 </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 34px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">2 lb. </span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 170px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Feed (3 shots), Light</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.R1ekSNyjgw3v0svx]{Feed 3 shots}&nbsp;@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.bY9owuVfWrNWp8NV]{Light}</p>",
